ZCZC EE18
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 082300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A LARGE DEEP LOW LIES CENTRED 979 WERN
SOLE BRINGING STRG WINDS TO ALL OF NITON WITH GALES
POSS IN LUNDY FASTNET AND SHANNON. OVERNIGHT SUNDAY AND
DURING MONDAY THE LOW MOVS SW AND BEGINS TO FILL LYING
CENTRED 983 W OF FITZROY MONDAY EVENING WHILE A NEW
SHALLOW LOW DEVELOPS IN THE ENGLISH CHANNEL. STRG WINDS
EASE IN THE ENGLISH CHANNEL BUT PERSIST ELSEWHERE WITH
GALES EASING IN LUNDY FASTNET AND SHANNON. OVERNIGHT
MONDAY STRG WINDS BECMG CONFINED TO FITZROY AND SOLE AS
THE LARGE LOW FILLS WHILE THE SHALLOW LOW IN THE ENGLISH
CHANNEL MOVS N ALLOWING STRG WINDS TO PERSIST IN THE
IRISH SEA. DURING TUESDAY DAYTIME STRG WINDS PERSIST IN
FITZROY. THE SHALLOW LOW FILLS WITH STRG WINDS EASING IN
THE IRISH SEA. LITTLE CHANGE EXP OVERNIGHT TUESDAY AND
DURING WEDNESDAY WITH STRG WINDS PERSISTING IN FITZROY
BUT LIGHT WINDS ELSEWHERE
NNNN